{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"Tile store enabled for accessing local tile packs and for loading new tile packs from server.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"readAndUpdate","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All tile requests are converted to tile pack requests, i.e.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the tile pack that includes the request tile will be loaded, and the tile extracted"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"from it. In this mode, no individual tile requests will be made."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This mode can be useful if the map trajectory is predefined and the user cannot pan"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"freely (e.g. navigation use cases), so that there is a good chance tile packs are already loaded","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the vicinity of the user."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If users can pan freely, this mode is not recommended. Otherwise, panning"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will download tile packs instead of using individual tiles. Note that this means that we could first"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"download an individual tile, and then a tile pack that also includes this tile. The individual tile in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the disk cache won’t be used as long as the up-to-date tile pack exists in the cache."}]}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/TileStoreUsageMode\/readAndUpdate","interfaceLanguage":"s